<F P=103> OW0106034494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Valletta, May 31 (XINHUA) -- Maltese President Dr. 
Ugo Mifsud Bonnici met here today with a delegation from the 
National People's Congress of China (NPC) led by vice-chairman 
of the Standing Committee of the NPC, Wang Guangying. 
  During the meeting Bonnici spoke highly of China's great 
achievements in many areas since the adoption of the reform and 
opening policy in the late 1970s. 
  Bonnici and Wang both stressed that further development of 
friendly relations between Malta and China would promote the two 
nations' economic development and world peace and stability. 
  They also discussed bilateral cooperation in the fields of 
politics, the economy and culture as well as international 
issues of mutual concern. 
  Earlier, the speaker of the Maltese parliament also met with 
Wang and his party. 
  The Chinese delegation arrived here on Monday after visiting 
Portugal. 

</TEXT>

