<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Madrid, May 31 (XINHUA) -- Spanish Trade and Tourism 
Minister Javier Navarro said here today that his government 
regards China as one of the most favorite nations with which to 
develop economic and trade relations. 
  Addressing a seminar on the potential of the Chinese market, 
Navarro urged Spanish entrepreneurs to strive to increase their 
investment in China and to promote bilateral trade. 
  He pointed out that China is a developing nation with a 
population of over 1.1 billion, and that the Spanish government 
will assist businesses to take advantage of the opportunities 
available. 
  Song Guoqing, the Chinese ambassador to Spain, and more than 
200 Spanish businessmen attended the seminar. 

