GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0206010594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Beijing, 31 May (XINHUA) -- Comrade Li Chuli, 
former member of the Standing Committee of the National 
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative 
Conference [CPPCC] and deputy head of the International Liaison 
Department of the CPC Central Committee, died of illness in 
Beijing on 15 May at the age of 95. [passage omitted] 

